00:54:05,985 --> 00:54:08,988
What? Is she really his sponsor?

758
00:54:10,156 --> 00:54:12,450
Tae-woong, we really need to go.

759
00:54:13,159 --> 00:54:15,203
Fine. Let's go.

760
00:54:15,995 --> 00:54:18,373
Kang Baek…

761
00:54:20,792 --> 00:54:22,877
Lee Yeong…

762
00:54:23,378 --> 00:54:25,838
LEE YEONG-HWA

763
00:54:32,303 --> 00:54:34,639
LEE YEONG-HWA

764
00:54:36,724 --> 00:54:37,892
I got you.

765
00:54:38,393 --> 00:54:40,478
FOLLOW

766
00:54:41,604 --> 00:54:42,855
What?

767
00:54:43,898 --> 00:54:46,150
There are no photos of you.
Are you not confident?

768
00:54:50,113 --> 00:54:51,114
Wait.

769
00:54:55,493 --> 00:54:57,745
Please send it over by Friday.
I'll confirm it.

770
00:54:59,247 --> 00:55:00,248
Goodbye.

771
00:55:18,141 --> 00:55:19,308
KI SEON-GYEOM

772
00:55:19,392 --> 00:55:20,309
He's--

773
00:55:20,810 --> 00:55:24,272
Sell me the new painting at the cafe.
The owner told me to discuss with you.

774
00:55:25,982 --> 00:55:27,525
You can speak casually to me.

775
00:55:30,903 --> 00:55:33,031
-Here you are.
-You refused to paint a new one,

776
00:55:33,114 --> 00:55:34,532
so just sell that to me.

777
00:55:36,034 --> 00:55:38,327
You like my painting that much?

778
00:55:42,540 --> 00:55:44,417
What happened here?

779
00:55:45,209 --> 00:55:47,170
I didn't know it was wet and touched it.

780
00:55:47,253 --> 00:55:49,922
Don't you know that drying is
the most important step in oil painting?

781
00:55:51,007 --> 00:55:53,342
It was for school,
and I hung it right after.

782
00:55:53,426 --> 00:55:55,803
Art students often don't have the time
to dry their paintings

783
00:55:55,887 --> 00:55:57,847
as the assignments have a tight deadline.

784
00:55:57,930 --> 00:56:01,225
Seeing how you took the painting anyway,
you must really like it.

785
00:56:02,060 --> 00:56:04,729
I do. I see time in your paintings.

786
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:07,231
You see, I value time the most.

787
00:56:09,984 --> 00:56:12,528
If you're not going to sell it,

788
00:56:14,197 --> 00:56:17,366
I'd like my ten million won in cash.

789
00:56:18,785 --> 00:56:21,370
Right. You could sell your painting
for just as much.

790
00:56:21,454 --> 00:56:22,789
-That's good, right?
-Pardon?

791
00:56:23,915 --> 00:56:25,792
It's a bit much for my painting.

792
00:56:25,875 --> 00:56:27,126
Then give me the change.

793
00:56:27,210 --> 00:56:29,545
And buyers are the ones
who put the price on them.

794
00:56:29,629 --> 00:56:32,215
If I say it's worth ten million,
then that's that.

795
00:56:34,675 --> 00:56:36,344
-Why me?
-What do you mean?

796
00:56:36,427 --> 00:56:37,512
Why my painting?

797
00:56:38,096 --> 00:56:41,265
Someone like you could ask
Monet or Picasso for one.

798
00:56:41,349 --> 00:56:42,517
They're dead.

799
00:56:46,145 --> 00:56:47,271
I'm not selling it.

800
00:56:49,565 --> 00:56:52,485
You don't want to paint or sell.
What is it? Are you rich?

801
00:56:52,568 --> 00:56:54,362
Hear me out, will you?

802
00:56:54,445 --> 00:56:56,906
I drew that for the cafe.

803
00:56:56,989 --> 00:56:59,951
If it's displayed anywhere else,
it loses its meaning.

804
00:57:01,494 --> 00:57:04,247
What if it was placed
at Seomyung Art Museum?

805
00:57:04,330 --> 00:57:05,373
I don't care…

806
00:57:07,208 --> 00:57:09,919
What was that again? Seomyung Art Museum?

807
00:57:10,711 --> 00:57:12,588
I'm going there?

808
00:57:12,672 --> 00:57:13,714
Your painting, not you.

809
00:57:22,265 --> 00:57:23,808
My goodness.

810
00:57:25,059 --> 00:57:27,437
You should improve
your communication skills.

811
00:57:28,020 --> 00:57:32,066
What I meant was that
I'd rather paint you a new one.

812
00:57:32,150 --> 00:57:35,570
That was what I was about to say.

813
00:57:35,653 --> 00:57:37,780
You rejected me before.
You must be quite materialistic.

814
00:57:37,864 --> 00:57:38,906
I was playing hard to get.

815
00:57:38,990 --> 00:57:41,826
If I said yes right away,
I would've looked desperate.

816
00:57:43,035 --> 00:57:45,663
This is why I'm so disgusted by artists.

817
00:57:45,746 --> 00:57:48,332
Give me your number. I need to speak
with you to get the drawing you want.

818
00:57:48,416 --> 00:57:49,709
You can call Mr. Jeong.

819
00:57:49,792 --> 00:57:52,003
You spoke to him,
so you must have his number.

820
00:57:54,505 --> 00:57:57,300
You should go.
Give me the rough sketch by this week.

821
00:58:01,471 --> 00:58:02,889
Thanks for the robe.

822
00:58:04,765 --> 00:58:06,601
Hey, about the rough… Answer…

823
00:58:07,268 --> 00:58:08,561
Hey, kid.

824
00:58:29,165 --> 00:58:32,210
FIVE HUNDRED THOUSAND WON

825
00:58:39,550 --> 00:58:42,386
CHILAN MOUNTAIN BEEKEEPING

826
00:58:49,685 --> 00:58:52,063
<i>My parents are beekeepers
and sent me too many.</i>

827
00:58:52,146 --> 00:58:53,022
<i>It's pure honey.</i>

828
00:58:53,105 --> 00:58:55,691
<i>I know the number on your card
is for business.</i>

829
00:58:55,775 --> 00:58:57,318
<i>Reply with your private number.</i>

830
00:59:02,198 --> 00:59:05,076
Mr. Jeong, please check
the origin of this ingredient.

831
00:59:05,159 --> 00:59:06,744
You know I'm careful about what I eat.

832
00:59:14,043 --> 00:59:15,253
What is that?

833
00:59:15,753 --> 00:59:17,505
Is that how it's going to be?

834
00:59:17,588 --> 00:59:19,131
You shouldn't do that
when you're unemployed.

835
00:59:19,215 --> 00:59:22,009
I thought bringing these would help.

836
00:59:22,093 --> 00:59:23,803
What do you mean? Bring them where?

837
00:59:25,137 --> 00:59:26,973
I need my teacher's help.

838
00:59:27,056 --> 00:59:29,475
I'm going to meet with her
and ask for a favor.

839
00:59:29,559 --> 00:59:32,353
I'm so lost right now.
Does she live far away?

840
00:59:32,436 --> 00:59:33,646
Not really.

841
00:59:34,397 --> 00:59:36,399
When will you be done with your project?

842
00:59:37,483 --> 00:59:39,485
I'm trying to finish it by tonight.

843
00:59:39,569 --> 00:59:41,362
That way, I can have fun in peace.

844
00:59:41,445 --> 00:59:43,072
The weather's lovely these days.

845
00:59:43,155 --> 00:59:46,033
Do you want to come with me?
You can get some fresh air.

846
00:59:46,951 --> 00:59:48,869
Am I allowed to go?

847
00:59:49,829 --> 00:59:51,455
I don't feel too confident alone.

848
00:59:51,998 --> 00:59:53,457
There's a lot that I don't know.

849
00:59:55,001 --> 00:59:57,336
Eun-bi lent me her car

850
00:59:57,962 --> 00:59:59,547
and told me to get some fresh air.

851
01:00:01,549 --> 01:00:03,926
How nice of you to try and clock me out.

852
01:00:04,510 --> 01:00:07,346
Since I don't have a boss,
I clock out when I think I should.

853
01:00:07,430 --> 01:00:09,599
But when I do, I feel bad.

854
01:00:11,142 --> 01:00:13,644
That schedule of yours
is quite problematic.

855
01:00:14,687 --> 01:00:17,523
Write that you'll get off work
at 9 a.m. tomorrow.

856
01:00:18,149 --> 01:00:20,776
Yes. I'll make sure to get it done by then.

857
01:00:21,527 --> 01:00:23,237
I'm excited to work now.

858
01:00:31,078 --> 01:00:32,622
<i>This is nice.</i>

859
01:00:49,180 --> 01:00:50,931
<i>You have arrived at your destination.</i>

860
01:00:51,015 --> 01:00:53,267
-<i>Ending navigation.</i>
-Apparently, we're here.

861
01:00:53,351 --> 01:00:55,102
I don't think this is correct.

862
01:00:55,186 --> 01:00:57,688
It's the right address.

863
01:00:58,522 --> 01:00:59,565
What should we do?

864
01:01:00,566 --> 01:01:01,692
One minute.

865
01:01:06,405 --> 01:01:08,616
I should look around a bit more.

866
01:01:08,699 --> 01:01:10,117
It's the correct address.

867
01:01:10,201 --> 01:01:13,371
It's blazing hot.
Let's have some ice cream.

868
01:01:13,454 --> 01:01:14,747
There was a mart back there.

869
01:01:14,830 --> 01:01:18,417
You can wait there while I look around.

870
01:01:18,501 --> 01:01:19,502
Okay.

871
01:01:23,839 --> 01:01:25,049
I bought some ice cream.

872
01:01:25,132 --> 01:01:28,302
GAMA MART

873
01:01:29,261 --> 01:01:30,346
Sit down.

874
01:01:30,930 --> 01:01:32,139
Good boy.

875
01:02:31,741 --> 01:02:32,950
"One hundred seventy-two."

876
01:02:35,578 --> 01:02:36,620
Is anyone in?

877
01:02:37,997 --> 01:02:39,081
Ms. Bang?

878
01:02:58,517 --> 01:02:59,560
Ms. Bang.

879
01:03:03,272 --> 01:03:04,440
Ms. Oh.

880
01:03:05,149 --> 01:03:07,067
Why are you with her?

881
01:03:07,151 --> 01:03:08,444
I picked her up on my way.

882
01:03:09,195 --> 01:03:10,488
It's been a long time.

883
01:03:10,571 --> 01:03:13,324
I was worried I couldn't find you

884
01:03:13,407 --> 01:03:15,367
since you lived in seclusion.

885
01:03:15,451 --> 01:03:18,662
It's not that. It's just hard
to get a connection here.

886
01:03:19,288 --> 01:03:21,624
Have you eaten?

887
01:03:22,708 --> 01:03:24,043
No.

888
01:03:35,679 --> 01:03:39,391
I don't have much,
but this drink is expensive.

889
01:03:41,101 --> 01:03:43,646
-Can you handle alcohol better now?
-A bit.

890
01:03:45,606 --> 01:03:48,234
Goodness, he's such a gentleman.

891
01:03:48,317 --> 01:03:51,529
What kind of gentleman peels fruit?
They won't even go near the kitchen.

892
01:03:51,612 --> 01:03:53,197
Can you drink?

893
01:03:53,280 --> 01:03:54,907
He's boring
since he can't handle his drink.

894
01:03:54,990 --> 01:03:57,159
I enjoy drinking.

895
01:03:57,243 --> 01:03:58,953
I'll be your drinking buddy.

896
01:04:01,580 --> 01:04:03,207
This must be expensive.

897
01:04:04,250 --> 01:04:06,502
It seems like yesterday when we first met.

898
01:04:07,211 --> 01:04:09,880
I can't believe
you became a national athlete.

899
01:04:09,964 --> 01:04:13,592
Ms. Bang, we met for the first time
during your farewell match.

900
01:04:13,676 --> 01:04:15,886
It was the National Sports Festival.

901
01:04:15,970 --> 01:04:18,556
I was so shocked when I saw you.

902
01:04:18,639 --> 01:04:21,308
I thought Jeong-do had adopted you.

903
01:04:22,393 --> 01:04:25,354
You should seriously thank your mom.

904
01:04:30,025 --> 01:04:32,486
Who knew he'd become a politician?

905
01:04:33,529 --> 01:04:36,574
Never mind. I did see it coming.

906
01:04:40,870 --> 01:04:44,039
Drink up, will you?
Did you come here to peel fruit?

907
01:04:50,296 --> 01:04:51,589
I still have some.

908
01:04:55,426 --> 01:04:59,346
Ms. Bang, a track and field
coaching position is currently vacant.

909
01:04:59,430 --> 01:05:03,142
I was wondering if you could
take that position.

910
01:05:03,225 --> 01:05:06,520
I've been doing charity for them
for the past five years.

911
01:05:06,604 --> 01:05:10,357
Some of them are worth being nurtured
for the national team.

912
01:05:10,441 --> 01:05:13,360
Goodness, you did well. I'm proud of you.

913
01:05:14,403 --> 01:05:18,490
What a shame. I enjoy my current life.

914
01:05:18,574 --> 01:05:20,200
I don't want to get involved again.

915
01:05:20,284 --> 01:05:23,037
Ms. Bang, there are many prospects
in that team.

916
01:05:23,120 --> 01:05:24,330
There are many girls too,

917
01:05:24,413 --> 01:05:27,249
-so I think it's best--
-I don't want to hear it.

918
01:05:29,710 --> 01:05:32,004
-Ms. Bang, I--
-Get out. Go.

919
01:05:33,172 --> 01:05:34,006
Ma'am.

920
01:05:36,342 --> 01:05:38,260
This gentleman…

921
01:05:39,011 --> 01:05:40,429
Wait, what was his name again?

922
01:05:40,512 --> 01:05:42,640
-Seon-gyeom.
-"Seon-gyeom"?

923
01:05:42,723 --> 01:05:44,224
Did you know that he came in last?

924
01:05:46,352 --> 01:05:48,020
Do you or do you not?

925
01:05:48,103 --> 01:05:51,482
Of course, I do.
His record improved thanks to me.

926
01:05:52,191 --> 01:05:54,777
No way. I didn't know that.

927
01:05:56,195 --> 01:05:57,905
You're completely wasted, aren't you?

928
01:05:59,990 --> 01:06:01,283
You see…

929
01:06:02,201 --> 01:06:07,831
Listening to you, I couldn't help
but be curious.

930
01:06:08,332 --> 01:06:11,460
Since he didn't ask, I will.

931
01:06:13,128 --> 01:06:18,342
Why don't you want to get involved again?

932
01:06:18,968 --> 01:06:23,138
You made a boy who came last
into a national athlete.

933
01:06:23,222 --> 01:06:25,224
That shows how good you are.

934
01:06:25,307 --> 01:06:27,726
So why are you refusing his offer?

935
01:06:29,019 --> 01:06:30,938
Who gave you a tough time?

936
01:06:31,021 --> 01:06:34,316
Who hurt you?

937
01:06:34,400 --> 01:06:36,402
I'm going to kill them all.

938
01:06:38,570 --> 01:06:39,530
Goodness.

939
01:06:44,827 --> 01:06:45,869
Ms. Oh.

940
01:06:47,329 --> 01:06:49,581
-Take her with you!
-Yes, ma'am.

941
01:06:51,792 --> 01:06:52,876
Get up.

942
01:06:53,544 --> 01:06:55,337
This way. Over here.

943
01:06:59,341 --> 01:07:01,260
-Are you okay?
-Let me go.

944
01:07:01,343 --> 01:07:02,469
I didn't touch you.

945
01:07:05,723 --> 01:07:06,682
Ms. Oh.

946
01:07:07,683 --> 01:07:10,185
It's a dead-end that way.
Where are you going?

947
01:07:10,853 --> 01:07:11,895
Ms. Oh.

948
01:07:29,747 --> 01:07:30,831
Ms. Oh?

949
01:07:31,749 --> 01:07:33,042
Wake up for a minute.

950
01:07:34,793 --> 01:07:37,254
Have some water. Here.

951
01:07:37,337 --> 01:07:39,465
What? It's not cold.

952
01:07:40,758 --> 01:07:43,135
You should've refused
if you couldn't take it.

953
01:07:43,218 --> 01:07:44,970
She can drink you under the table.

954
01:07:49,349 --> 01:07:52,728
Let me look around
for a bed and breakfast.

955
01:07:52,811 --> 01:07:55,397
Wait here. I'll be back soon.

956
01:08:00,611 --> 01:08:01,612
Don't go.

957
01:08:11,914 --> 01:08:13,207
I don't know. I just…

958
01:08:14,833 --> 01:08:16,293
I'm worried you'll disappear.

959
01:08:20,839 --> 01:08:22,049
I won't.

960
01:08:22,883 --> 01:08:24,635
You drank so much for me.

961
01:08:32,976 --> 01:08:36,688
To be honest, I wanted to help out.

962
01:08:37,272 --> 01:08:38,190
That's a lie.

963
01:08:40,025 --> 01:08:42,111
I wanted to see more of you.

964
01:08:43,112 --> 01:08:48,075
If I get drunk and go to bed early,

965
01:08:48,158 --> 01:08:49,910
then I'd wake up early as well.

966
01:08:51,703 --> 01:08:55,541
By doing that, I'd get to see you more.

967
01:09:00,462 --> 01:09:01,839
Gosh, my head.

968
01:09:02,840 --> 01:09:04,174
Do you want more water?

969
01:09:05,259 --> 01:09:06,844
-Are you cold?
-No.

970
01:09:06,927 --> 01:09:08,095
Is there anything you need?

971
01:09:08,929 --> 01:09:10,305
I'll do everything I can.

972
01:09:11,473 --> 01:09:13,392
-Really?
-I'll try to.

973
01:09:14,685 --> 01:09:16,186
You're saying that again.

974
01:09:17,062 --> 01:09:18,063
You're…

975
01:09:19,189 --> 01:09:20,607
You're so hardworking.

976
01:09:22,693 --> 01:09:23,652
Then…

977
01:09:26,071 --> 01:09:27,239
can you…

978
01:09:29,700 --> 01:09:31,201
What did you say?

979
01:09:32,995 --> 01:09:34,121
Can you…

980
01:09:36,123 --> 01:09:37,374
like me?

981
01:09:45,924 --> 01:09:47,509
I already do.

982
01:10:40,562 --> 01:10:42,356
<i>You must live around here.</i>

983
01:10:42,439 --> 01:10:44,233
-Let me walk you home.
-He's like a baby.

984
01:10:44,316 --> 01:10:47,319
What is it about him that makes you
so protective of him?

985
01:10:47,402 --> 01:10:49,488
<i>-I never said I liked him.
-You don't remember.</i>

986
01:10:49,571 --> 01:10:50,572
How disappointing.

987
01:10:50,656 --> 01:10:53,492
<i>-She even invited us to the premier.</i>
-Go with him instead.

988
01:10:53,575 --> 01:10:54,993
<i>Seo Tae-woong, Seo Dan-ah…</i>

989
01:10:55,077 --> 01:10:56,787
<i>He was looking at you funny.</i>

990
01:10:56,870 --> 01:10:58,413
<i>Stop crossing the line.</i>

991
01:10:58,497 --> 01:11:00,374
<i>But you came to see me
because I crossed the line.</i>

992
01:11:00,457 --> 01:11:02,251
<i>Seon-gyeom! Where are you going?</i>

993
01:11:02,334 --> 01:11:05,963
-To see Ms. Seo?
-I guess he wants us to become a thing.

994
01:11:06,046 --> 01:11:08,715
<i>-Why the hospitality?
-Maybe I want something from you.</i>

995
01:11:09,508 --> 01:11:11,093
-Did you fight?
-Stop following me.

996
01:11:11,176 --> 01:11:12,761
<i>I guess it was just me again.</i>

997
01:11:12,844 --> 01:11:15,222
<i>What's with you and Ms. Seo?</i>

998
01:11:15,305 --> 01:11:17,182
I'm going to have Ms. Seo

999
01:11:17,266 --> 01:11:18,684
<i>marry Seon-gyeom.</i>

1000
01:11:18,767 --> 01:11:20,602
Stop using me as the means
to fulfil your dream.

1001
01:11:20,686 --> 01:11:22,229
<i>Should I file a missing persons report?</i>

1002
01:11:22,312 --> 01:11:25,232
Could he be crashing someplace else?

1003
